episodes.natural_language:
Case Jensen-Ott-MVA-8-6-2025 involves client Jensen Ott. On Wednesday, October 29, 2025, at 01:57:34 GMT-04:00, Aaron Whaley of Whaley Law Firm sent an email from agwhaley@whaleylawfirm.com to Justin Chumbley (Justin@whaleylawfirm.com) and to Jensen Ott’s Filevine project address JensenOttMVAZ5116960@louisvilleaccidentlawyer.filevineapp.com.

In the body of the message, Whaley writes that treatment with Starlight “might be done,” and he notes that some of the injured may have gone to primary care or were seeking MRIs or something. He proposes getting the records and bills from Starlight, assuming they are done, because there are three people involved. He also bets that the case involves minimum insurance limits and describes the accident as pretty bad. He adds that there’s no way the defendants would want to defend this dude, if you read the police report. The message ends with the signature of Aaron Whaley of the Whaley Law Firm, including the firm’s address at 712 Lyndon Ln, Louisville, KY 40222, and the phone number 502-583-4022.
